Document: VisualShaderNodeGroupBase
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodegroupbase.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available for managing input and output ports of a VisualShaderNodeGroupBase.

Method: add_input_port(id: int, type: int, name: String)
Adds an input port with the specified type (see PortType) and name.

Method: add_output_port(id: int, type: int, name: String)
Adds an output port with the specified type (see PortType) and name.

Method: clear_input_ports()
Removes all previously specified input ports.

Method: clear_output_ports()
Removes all previously specified output ports.

Method: get_free_input_port_id() → int |const|
Returns a free input port ID which can be used in add_input_port().

Method: get_free_output_port_id() → int |const|
Returns a free output port ID which can be used in add_output_port().

Method: get_input_port_count() → int |const|
Returns the number of input ports in use. Alternative for get_free_input_port_id().

Method: get_inputs() → String |const|
Returns a String description of the input ports as a colon-separated list using the format "id,type,name;" (see add_input_port()).

Method: get_output_port_count() → int |const|
Returns the number of output ports in use. Alternative for get_free_output_port_id().

Method: get_outputs() → String |const|
Returns a String description of the output ports as a colon-separated list using the format "id,type,name;" (see add_output_port()).

Method: has_input_port(id: int) → bool |const|
Returns true if the specified input port exists.

Method: has_output_port(id: int) → bool |const|
Returns true if the specified output port exists.

Method: is_valid_port_name(name: String) → bool |const|
Returns true if the specified port name does not override an existed port name and is valid within the shader.

Method: remove_input_port(id: int)
Removes the specified input port.

Method: remove_output_port(id: int)
Removes the specified output port.

Method: set_input_port_name(id: int, name: String)
Renames the specified input port.

Method: set_input_port_type(id: int, type: int)
Sets the specified input port's type (see PortType).

Method: set_inputs(inputs: String)
Defines all input ports using a String formatted as a colon-separated list: "id,type,name;" (see add_input_port()).

Method: set_output_port_name(id: int, name: String)
Renames the specified output port.

Method: set_output_port_type(id: int, type: int)
Sets the specified output port's type (see PortType).

Method: set_outputs(outputs: String)
Defines all output ports using a String formatted as a colon-separated list: "id,type,name;" (see add_output_port()).